Title: Series: Les Artistes Anciens et Modernes
Description: Titlepage to the eighth livraison; a figure standing in the light outside a building with a horseshoe and an ogival arch (?); possibly in North Africa or Egypt, seen through a garden with lush vegetation, including a tree with large leaves and exotic fruit and other vegetation; after Français Lithograph on grey chine collé
Curator's comments: The livraisons are sometimes described in French publications as 'volumes'. For further information on the series, including dating, see Curator’s Comment on 1936,0302.14.1.
Acquisition notes: 1880,0710.1 to 250 constitute a series of plates for 'Les artistes anciens et modernes' from 1842-60.
